They sat calmly in the court&rsquo;s third row, watching themselves on video detailing their years of torture and deprivation in squalid conditions.
One tearfully testified how, seven years after her rescue, she still requires twice weekly therapy. Another, more resilient, described herself as a survivor &mdash; a &ldquo;strong black woman&rdquo; determined to finally leave behind the Tacony dungeon of their shared nightmares.
